`[ExpectedException]` was removed in MSTest v4. Replace it with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>` inside the test body:

```csharp
// Before (v3)
[ExpectedException(typeof(InvalidOperationException))]
[TestMethod]
public void MyTest()
{
    service.DoWork();
}

// After (v4)
[TestMethod]
public void MyTest()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<InvalidOperationException>(() => service.DoWork());
}
```

**Key variants:**
- **Async methods** â†’ use `await Assert.ThrowsExactlyAsync<T>(() => ...)`
- **Allow derived exception types** (`AllowDerivedTypes = true`) â†’ use `Assert.Throws<T>` / `Assert.ThrowsAsync<T>` instead

> **Tip:** MSTest v3 analyzer `MSTEST0006` already flagged `[ExpectedException]` usage â€” you can fix these before upgrading to v4 so the migration is smoother.

